        [
          "You grew up in comfort outside Florence, you were supposed to take over father's vineyard, but then they came. It wasn't clear who you should support, but in the fray, you watched a woman attacked by several men hudreds of times her weight in stones. Whether it was compassion for her, or the voice that fired you to fight, you drove a plow through one of her assailant's chests. The ahses that fell through your hands like grapes off the vine only startled you, and you stilll dream sweetly of his horroified face. Your reward was the Embrace, and Elizabeth kept you close to her side, feeding the sultry voice that urged you to her aid. She refers to you as \"The man who will change everything\". She taught you about Caine, of course, but only to know of his insolence for scorning the Dark Mother, Lilith. You learned along side your brother, but he forfeith his path and memories to a Demon, whom he serves as faithfully as you serve Elizabeth and Lilith. But you believe there is a way to save Thiago, after all, you are the man who will change everything."
